avirus en Espa\u00f1a, en im\u00e1genes|newspaper = El Pa\u00eds|date = 27 March 2020|last1 = Pa\u00eds|first1 = El|access-date = 27 March 2020|archive-url = https://web.archive.org/web/20200327221007/https://elpais.com/elpais/2020/03/27/album/1585307949_171686.html#foto_gal_3|archive-date = 27 March 2020|url-status = live}}</ref>\n|-\n|{{SGP}} || || lockdown. Local returnees from all countries are required to be quarantined at designated locations for 14 days. Instructions for all local residents to stay at home. || April 7 || May 4 || <ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.nytimes.com/reuters/2020/04/03/world/asia/03reuters-health-coronavirus-singapore.html|title=Singapore closes workplaces, schools as coronavirus cases jump|website=The New York Times|date=3 April 2020|accessdate=5 April 2020}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.straitstimes.com/politics/ban-on-social-gatherings-of-any-size-in-homes-or-public-areas|title=Ban on social gatherings of any size in homes or public areas|website=The Straits Times|date=8 April 2020|accessdate=9 April 2020}}</ref>\n|-\n|{{SVK}} \n| || lockdown || April 8 || April 13 || <ref>http://www.uvzsr.sk/index.php?option=com_content&view=article&id=4178:covid-19-vony-pohyb-osob-na-verejnosti-bude-poas-vekononych-sviatkov-obmedzeny&catid=250:koronavirus-2019-ncov&Itemid=153</ref>\n|-\n|{{LKA}} || || curfew || || ||\n|-\n|{{SWI}} || || curfew || || ||\n|-\n|{{SYR}} || || curfew || || || <ref>{{cite web |title=Syria adds night curfew to coronavirus curbs |url=https://www.jpost.com/breaking-news/syria-adds-night-curfew-to-coronavirus-curbs-622342 |website=The Jerusalem Post}}</ref>\n|-\n|{{TUR}} || || curfew for under 20 aged people and over 65 aged people || || || <ref>{{cite web |title=https://www.hurriyet.com.tr/gundem/sokaga-cikma-yasagi-yas-araligi-nedir-sokaga-cikma-yasagi-cezasi-ne-kadar-41489708|website=Hurriyet |language=tr}}</ref>\n|-\n|{{TWN}} || || mandatory self-isolation || || ||\n|-\n|{{THA}} || || curfew from 22:00 to 4:00 